SD=Reward Points Account															
CR=Reward Points Log															
BQs= Expiration Capture															
Track/log the allocation and remittance of rewards points. The service domain acts as a transaction log similar where the instrument is not subject to interest considerations (as with cash) but may have a finite life-time with expiry dates on reward points															
"Example of use: A customer transaction that generates reward points is captured on the log, resulting in an increase in their available point balance"															
Administer the booking and remittance of rewards points															
CR Reward Points Log								BQ Expiration				BQ Capture			
In	Up	Co	Ec	Ca	Rq	Gr	Re	In	Up	Ca	Re	In	Up	Ca	Re
InCR Instantiate a new Reward Points Log															
UpCR Update details relating to Reward Points Log															
CoCR Control the processing of Reward Points Log															
EcCR Accept, verify, etc. aspects of Reward Points Log processing															
CaCR Capture Reward Points Log activity or event related information															
RqCR Request manual intervention or a decision with respect to Reward Points Log															
GrCR Obtain permission to act in relation to Reward Points Log															
ReCR Retrieve details about any aspect of Reward Points Log															
InBQ Instantiate a new Expiration															
UpBQ Update details relating to Expiration															
CaBQ Capture Expiration activity or event related information															
ReBQ Retrieve details about any aspect of Expiration															
InBQ Instantiate a new Capture															
UpBQ Update details relating to Capture															
CaBQ Capture Capture activity or event related information															
ReBQ Retrieve details about any aspect of Capture															